tweet: I agree this is a sensitive & difficult issue. No easy solutions. But a world that is "a little bit" better is still achievable. *SBY*

tweet: Many are sceptic & pessimistic. They say that its impossible for terriorism  & tension btwn Islam & the West be overcome. *SBY*

tweet: I trully hope that world leaders, including religious leaders, can do something. Let us prevent the worsening of situation in the world*SBY*

tweet: I invite any nation,America,Europe, Asia, Islam & others to choose a solution thats more wise & appropriate. It doesnt have to be war *SBY*

name: S. B. Yudhoyono
tweet: A few days ago, in the US, I conveyed this view to those that care & want to be part of the solution. *SBY*

name: S. B. Yudhoyono
tweet: Dont get me wrong, I also condemn the murder of the cartoonist. But I'm thinking of how to prevent it in the future. *SBY*

name: S. B. Yudhoyono
tweet: If we truly wish to prevent this from repeating, we also have to mention the caricature drawing of Prophet Muhammad as the cause. *SBY*

name: S. B. Yudhoyono
tweet: I follow the international media since the violence in Paris. What was underlined was the issue of freedom of speech *SBY*

name: S. B. Yudhoyono
tweet: In truth, its not only power that tends to corrupt". "Liberty too can corrupt. Absolute liberty can corrupt absolutely".*SBY*

name: S. B. Yudhoyono
tweet: In my view, freedom still has its limitations. I believe that is also the spirit in the Universal Declaration of Human Rights. *SBY*

name: S. B. Yudhoyono
tweet: Conversely, leaders in the West are responsible so the freedom isnt abused to defame Islam, ie: caricatures of the Prophet. *SBY*

name: S. B. Yudhoyono
tweet: In the future,leaders in Islam are responsible to prevent violence,especially murder eventhough the victims were deemed to insult Islam*SBY*

name: S. B. Yudhoyono
tweet: I love peace. I want the relations btwn Islam & West to be even better.Shouldnt the caricature of Prophet Muhammad have been prevented?*SBY*

name: S. B. Yudhoyono
tweet: For me, the burning of a Holy Book of any religion, is example of freedom gone overboard. It cant be tolerated. *SBY*

name: S. B. Yudhoyono
tweet: In my statement, I was accompanied by other religious leaders from Islam, Christians, Hindu, Buddhist & Confucian. All were angered. *SBY*

name: S. B. Yudhoyono
tweet: A few years ago, I made a statement of protest to the planned burning of the Quran by a religious figure in the US. *SBY*

name: S. B. Yudhoyono
tweet: To make a caricature of Prophet Muhammad not only angers the extremist & radicals, but also to all Muslims. *SBY*

name: S. B. Yudhoyono
tweet: In the future we must have mutual understanding & respect in different views. Be considerate. If not, the price is too high. *SBY*

name: S. B. Yudhoyono
tweet: Here lies the problem. There is a fundamental difference. There is a "clash of values" & "clash of perceptions". We must overcome this *SBY*

name: S. B. Yudhoyono
tweet: But for the Islamic world, that act is a defamation & blasphemous. That person must receive a sanction. *SBY*

name: S. B. Yudhoyono
tweet: For the West,the caricature of the Prophet Muhammad is part of freedom of speech or expression.It is absolute, it shouldnt be limited *SBY*

name: S. B. Yudhoyono
tweet: Drawing the Prophet Muhammad, especially a caricature, for Muslims is a taboo. This is valid for all Muslims. *SBY*

name: S. B. Yudhoyono
tweet: Returning to the murder of cartoonist in Paris, I understand the anger that exists. But with good intentions, let us explore the causes*SBY*

name: S. B. Yudhoyono
tweet: Indonesians, who are mostly Muslims, must progress, prosper & attain justice, in social & economic terms. *SBY*

name: S. B. Yudhoyono
tweet: In the future,the world communities must respect each others values & beliefs.Not to impose their own value system or faiths to others *SBY*
